Hold on. I figured it out.
The argument is that subjective perspective isn't a representation of art, because art as a whole is divided into segments based first upon medium and second upon style.
One can make a sculpture in a traditional realism style, or even lean towards and abstract style.
The same is true of painters and even manga artists. A drawing isn't manga just because it was produced by a japanese person: a drawing is manga because it was produced in the same traditional style that has been used for years by such artists.
Even the very artists opinion of an art style can be wrong, either through ignorance or misinformation. Art is objective, in a way; and although nobody has a right to declare whether art is truly good or truly bad, anyone with an education in art should be able to differentiate choices in medium and style and come to objective conclusions about what kind of art they are even viewing.

It's NOT an anime girl because he says it is... but it IS a cartoon girl because of the stylistic choice the artist used...
